<!-- ++++++++++ feature_for_datum_target_relationship +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.feature_for_datum_target_relationship">
	A <b>feature_for_datum_target_relationship</b> is a type of
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/>
	that defines the nominal integral feature for a 
	<express_ref linkend="shape_aspect_definition_schema:ir_express:shape_aspect_definition_schema.datum_target"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- related_shape_aspect -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.feature_for_datum_target_relationship.related_shape_aspect">
	an inherited attribute shal be of type
	<express_ref linkend="shape_aspect_definition_schema:ir_express:shape_aspect_definition_schema.datum_target"/>
	for the <b>feature_for_datum_target_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- UR1 -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.feature_for_datum_target_relationship.ur:UR1">
	The <b>related_shape_aspect</b> shall be unique within a population of <b>feature_for_datum_target_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- WR1 -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.feature_for_datum_target_relationship.wr:WR1">
	The 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship.relating_shape_aspect"/>
	and the
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship.related_shape_aspect"/>
	shall belong to the same 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.product_definition_shape"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- WR2 -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.feature_for_datum_target_relationship.wr:WR2">
	The 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship.relating_shape_aspect"/>
	shall have the attribute 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect.product_definitional"/>
	set to TRUE.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Geometric_tolerance_mim  Entity: placed_datum_target_feature  
   <express_ref linkend="geometric_tolerance:mim:Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature">
	A <b>placed_datum_target_feature</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="shape_aspect_definition_schema:ir_express:shape_aspect_definition_schema.datum_target"/>

 that represents the implicit definition of a datum target for tolerancing purposes. See ARM definition for <express_ref linkend="geometric_tolerance:arm:Geometric_tolerance_arm.Placed_target"/>

 for more information.
</ext_description>

 <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature.representation_associations">
the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/>

 that specifies a <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/>

 of the <b>placed_datum_target_feature</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Geometric_tolerance_mim  Entity: placed_datum_target_feature  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="geometric_tolerance:mim:Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature.wr:WR1">
	The description attribute of the <b>placed_datum_target_feature</b> shall be either 'point', 'line', 'rectangle', 'circle' or 'circular curve'.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Geometric_tolerance_mim  Entity: placed_datum_target_feature  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="geometric_tolerance:mim:Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature.wr:WR2">
	A <b>placed_datum_target_feature</b> shall have exactly one implicit representation, conveyed by a <express_ref linkend="shape_aspect_definition_schema:ir_express:shape_aspect_definition_schema.shape_representation_with_parameters"/>.
</ext_description>

 <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature.wr:WR3">
 The items of the implicit representation shall be consistent with the type of the <b>placed_datum_target_feature</b>.
</ext_description>


<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.get_shape_aspect_property_definition_representations">
The <b>get_shape_aspect_property_definition_representations</b> function returns the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_definition_representation"/>

 that refer to a given instance of <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/>, through their <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation.definition"/>

 attribute and an instance of <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/>.
<note>The type of the returned result is declared as a set of instances of <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/>

 but only instances of <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_definition_representation"/>

 are included in the returned result at run time.</note></ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.get_shape_aspect_property_definition_representations.s_a_instance">
the <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/>

 that is considered.
</ext_description>

 <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.valid_datum_target_parameters">
The <b>valid_datum_target_parameters</b> function evaluates whether the 
<express_ref linkend="shape_aspect_definition_schema:ir_express:shape_aspect_definition_schema.shape_representation_with_parameters"/>
 that is expected to convey the parameters of the 
datum feature contains the right items, according to the kind of datum feature that is defined.
<p>This representation shall contain:</p>
<ul>
<li>one <express_ref linkend="geometry_schema:ir_express:geometry_schema.placement"/>
 with a name of 'orientation';</li>
<li>if the type of the feature is 'point', it shall not contain any other item;</li>
<li>if the type of the feature is 'line', it shall contain, in addition, one composite instance of <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/>

 and <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/>

 with a name of 'target length';</li>
<li>if the type of the feature is 'circle' or 'circular curve', it shall contain, in addition, one composite instance of <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/>

 and <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/>

 with a name of 'target diameter';</li>
<li>if the type of the feature is 'rectangle', it shall contain, in addition, one composite instance of <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/>

 and <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/>

 with a name of 'target width' and 
one composite instance of <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/>

 and <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/>

 with a name of 'target length'.</li>
</ul>
The function returns TRUE if these constraints are fulfilled, FALSE otherwise.
</ext_description>

 <ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.valid_datum_target_parameters.pdf">
the <express_ref linkend="geometric_tolerance:mim:Geometric_tolerance_mim.placed_datum_target_feature"/>

 that is considered and checked.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ tolerance_zone_form_name_constraint +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.tolerance_zone_form_name_constraint">
	The <b>tolerance_zone_form_name_constraint</b> rule ensures that each 
	<express_ref linkend="shape_tolerance_schema:ir_express:shape_tolerance_schema.tolerance_zone_form"/>
	has a name that is either
    'within a circle',
    'between two concentric circles',
    'between two equidistant curves',
    'within a cylinder',
    'between two coaxial cylinders',
    'between two equidistant surfaces',
    'non uniform',
    'cylindrical or circular',
    'spherical' or
    'unknown'.
</ext_description>
<!-- WR1 -->
<ext_description linkend="Geometric_tolerance_mim.tolerance_zone_form_name_constraint.wr:WR1">
	The local pass pariable shall evaluate to TRUE.
</ext_description>


